<title>SOUTH AFRICA: Afcol yr shr, div drops.</title>
<headline>Afcol yr shr, div drops.</headline>
<dateline>JOHANNESBURG 1997-05-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ended March 31</p>
<p>			(million rand unless stated)</p>
<p>    Shr, attrib (cts)     123.9	 vs 194.6</p>
<p>    Div (cts)	    14 making 62   vs 101.5</p>
<p>    Attrib income	   33.06	 vs 51.45</p>
<p>    Pre-tax		   43.97	 vs 70.76</p>
<p>    Tax			 17.17	 vs 23.44</p>
<p>    Interest paid	    1.17	 vs  4.73</p>
<p>    Turnover	     1,150.04	 vs 1,102.49</p>
<p>Div payable July 2 on register May 30</p>
<p>Full name: Associated Furniture Companies Ltd</p>
<p>NOTE - The company said current forecasts indicate that local demand for furniture will be uncertain in the new year but actions taken to improve performance, coupled with an expected rise in exports, should enable Afcol to post a satisfactory recovery in attributable earnings in the new financial year.</p>
<p>-- Johannesburg newsroom +27 11 482 1003</p>
